                     <interp inst="def1-663-18390204" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN KENT</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390204-663-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390204-663-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390204-663-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390204-cd-118" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-663-offence-1 t18390204-cd-118"></join>23rd of January</rs>, 1000 sheets of printed paper, value 9<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 100 maps, value 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390204-name-745" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-745" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-745" type="surname" value="WATKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-745" type="given" value="LOUISA MARGARET"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-663-offence-1 t18390204-name-745"></join>Louisa Margaret Watkins</persName>.—Another <hi rend="smallCaps">COUNT</hi>, stating them to be the goods of <persName id="t18390204-name-746" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-746" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-746" type="surname" value="WATKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-746" type="given" value="LOUISA MARGARET"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-663-offence-1 t18390204-name-746"></join>Louisa Margaret Watkins</persName> and another.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. GASELEE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-747" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-747" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-747" type="surname" value="WATKINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-747" type="given" value="THOMAS JOHN"></interp>THOMAS JOHN WATKINS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my sister Louisa Margaret Wat<lb></lb>kins, in St. John's-square—she carries on the business of a book-binder. On the 23rd of January, I was going home about seven o'clock, and saw a truck standing at my sister's door—I saw the prisoner go to the truck, take from it a parcel, put it on his shoulder, and walk away—I called out to know what he was about to do, upon which he ran away—when he had</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183902040110"></xptr>
               <p>run a few yards, he dropped the parcel and ran up St. John's-court—I pur<lb></lb>sued him, and he was either knocked down, or stopped by a man—I came up and took him back—I saw the parcel in the place where I saw him drop it—I never lost sight of him till I caught him, or not for two seconds.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you lose sight of the parcel? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not after it was taken up—I did not lose sight of the prisoner when he turned up the passage—it is my firm impression that I did not lose sight of him at all.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was the person running mixed with others? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, he was alone, and in the passage there was only myself, the prisoner, and the man who stopped him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-748" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-748" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-748" type="surname" value="GREENGRASS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-748" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH GREENGRASS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 90.) I was sent for on the night in question to take the prisoner—Mr. Watkins delivered this parcel to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did not he deny that he had taken the parcel? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, when I took him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">ARNOLD</hi>. I am in the employ of Johnson and Barrett, printers, in Mark-lane. On the 23rd of January I delivered four parcels to Joseph Ward—one of them was very similar to the one now produced.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-749" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-749" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-749" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-749" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH JOHNSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the printer of this work. Our servant seat some parcels to Miss Watkins to be bound—it is "Pilkington's Travels."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-750" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-750" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-750" type="surname" value="WALKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-750" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH WALKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Miss Watkins. On the night of the 23rd of January I received four parcels—this one is similar to one I had—I took them to Miss Watkins in St. John's-square—I took one parcel in, and when I came back there was one gone from the truck.</p>
               <p>
